> Get ready for a plate of pasta-tively delicious and super speedy ravioli! These
> carby pillows are stuffed with creamy ricotta and tomato, then coated in a
> luscious kale tomato sauce. Plus, it all comes together in under 20
> minutes—we're pretty sure you'll get some rave-ioli reviews for tonight's
> quick meal.

Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{to taste} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop half the leaves
into bite-size pieces. Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced) into ¼-inch pieces. Peel and
mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

Once water is boiling, add @fresh tomato ricotta ravioli{9%ounce} to pot.
Immediately reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until ravioli
are tender and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon} in a large pan
over medium-high heat. Add chopped kale and tomato; season with half the
@Tuscan heat spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of
@pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water;
cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @butter{2%tablespoon},
and a squeeze of lemon juice until melted and combined.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a
> splash at a time.

While veggies cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels;
season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan
over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Gently stir drained ravioli into pan with sauce until coated.

Divide ravioli between plates and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the
side.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise; stir into pan along with ravioli.